We recently took in a stray cat who was very overheated and looked like he might die. 

He is very scared, and won't let us come near him at all. He hides under everything, and won't come out almost all day except to eat and use the litterbox. 

Taking care of this cat has made me have more compassion for myself, and for people who have hurt my feelings in the past. 

We can often lash out because we are scared, or tired, or because we've been hurt in the past. 

Just because this cat isn't friendly, doesn't mean he deserves to be treated poorly. 

Just because I can be grumpy, or upset doesn't mean I need to treat myself poorly. 

Just as with the cat it takes time, care and a safe environment to slowly build trust, especially if we have been hurt in the past. 

Also, I am sorry if this comic is a bit depressing. I wrote it when I was feeling very vulnerable. I'm working on social anxiety with my therapist right now, and this comic was a result of my journaling practice. 

#comic #socialanxiety #therapy #cptsd

Small life update:
I've been slowly building my brand @kinkangifts which is a boutique that imports unique gifts and goods from Japan. 

I've been having a lot of fun and learning a lot doing in-person markets, and also have my brand in @themerchantile in Phoenix. 

Since I was laid off and my last work day is Dec 31, I am considering how I can make this my part-time and eventually full-time gig. 

Starting this store has been such a rewarding experience so far because I get to support small Japanese businesses, as well as interact directly with my community in Phoenix, meeting a ton of other small vendors and participating in local markets. 

Thank you to everyone who has been supportive of me in my business so far, and I really hope I can make this work!

It's that time of year again. 💕 
I haven't posted in a long time, as I have been busy planning on my retail store @kinkangifts opening soon. Been training for a marathon as well but will have more free time next year. I've been thinking of what I want to do with Just Peachy moving forward and might have more comics to share with you soon. 

Hope everyone is taking time to rest and relax.
